'''Ali Iyad Ali Olwan''' ({{langx|ar|علي إياد علي علوان}}; born 26 March 2000) is a Jordanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (football)|forward]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].<ref name="NFT">{{NFT player|80403|access-date=7 June 2021}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Olwan was a product of [[Amman]] based clubs [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al-Wehdat]] and later [[Al-Jazeera Club (Jordan)|Al-Jazeera]]. In July 2020, he was promoted to Al-Jazeera's first time at the age of 18.<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 July 2021|title=في حوار خاص لـ " الملاعب " .. مهاجم الجزيرة علي علوان يكشف قصة مغادرته الوحدات ومشاكل الجزيرة ومنتخب " النشامى " !! صور وفيديو |url=https://www.almeedansport.com/more-50790-1-%D9%81%D9%8A%20%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1%20%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B5%20%D9%84%D9%80%20%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%20%20..%20%D9%85%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%85%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9%20%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%20%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%20%D9%8A%D9%83%D8%B4%D9%81%20%D9%82%D8%B5%D8%A9%20%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AA%D9%87%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA%20%D9%88%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%84%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9%20%D9%88%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8%20%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89%20%20!%20%D8%B5%D9%88%D8%B1%20%D9%88%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%88|access-date=7 February 2024|website=almeedansport.com|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=14 December 2021|title=الجزيرة يوضح موقفه من احتراف علي علوان |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1094825/|access-date=7 February 2024|publisher=Koora|language=ar}}</ref>

=== Al-Shamal ===
In January 2022, Olwan joined [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Al-Shamal SC|Al-Shamal]] in a 2.5 years contract for a reported transfer fee of €200,000.<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 December 2021|title=الموافقة على انتقال علي علوان لنادٍ خليجي|url=https://royanews.tv/news/265207#google_vignette|access-date=7 February 2024|website=royalnews.tv|language=ar}}</ref>

=== Selangor ===
Following his expiring contract with Al-Shamal, Olwan moved abroad to Malaysia and joined [[Malaysia Super League]] club [[Selangor F.C.|Selangor]] on 5 August 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://selangorfc.com/en/news/3473/Ali%20Olwan%20IsRed |title=Ali Olwan #IsRed |publisher=Selangor FC |website=selangorfc.com |date=5 August 2024 |access-date=6 August 2024}}</ref> On 14 September, Olwan scored on his debut for the club in a 4–0 league win over [[Kuching City F.C.|Kuching City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/sports/football/2024/09/1105449/red-giants-trample-kuching-4-0 |title=Red Giants trample Kuching 4-0 |publisher=New Straits Times |website=nst.com.my |date=14 September 2024 |access-date=14 September 2024 |first=Farah |last=Azharie}}</ref> During the [[2024–25 AFC Champions League Two]] fixture against Korean giants [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors]] on 23 October 2024, Olwan scored a goal to secure a 2–1 win for Selangor.

===Al-Karma===
On 25 July 2025, Olwan joined [[Iraq Stars League]] club [[Al-Karma SC|Al-Karma]] on a one-year $450,000 contract, with an option for an additional season.<ref>{{cite web |title=مصادر عراقية: علي علوان ينضم إلى الكرمة العراقي بعقد ضخم للموسم الجديد |url=https://royanews.tv/news/354734 |website=royanews.tv |publisher=Roya News |access-date=26 July 2025 |language=Arabic |date=25 July 2025}}</ref>

===Al-Sailiya===
On 24 January 2025, Olwan returned to Qatar to join [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]].<ref>{{cite web |title=هداف كأس العرب يعزز هجوم السيلية القطري لتعويض الجزائري بن يطو |url=https://www.aljazeera.net/sport/2026/1/24/%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9 |website=aljazeera.net |publisher=Al-Jazeera |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=24 January 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
On 12 November 2020, Olwan made his international debut with [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] in a goalless [[friendly (association football)|friendly]] draw against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]].

On 4 September 2021, Olwan scored his first international goal against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]] at the [[Bahrain National Stadium]]. On 6 October 2021, Olwan scored his first professional career hat-trick in a 4–0 win against [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia]] at the [[Amman International Stadium]]. A month later, Olwan participated in the [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]], reaching the quarter-finals with Jordan.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-11-30|title=  استدعاء شرارة إلى المنتخب بعد إصابة العوضات بكورونا |url=https://www.hala.jo/2021/11/30/استدعاء-شرارة-إلى-المنتخب-بعد-إصابة-ا/|access-date=2021-11-30|website=هلا.جو|language=ar}}</ref>

In January 2024, Olwan was named in Jordan's squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] that reached the final.<ref>{{cite news|title=قائمة النشامى لنهائيات كأس آسيا 🇯🇴|trans-title=Al-Nashama list for the Asian Cup Finals 🇯🇴|url=https://twitter.com/JordanFA/status/1741356148530299195|publisher=Jordan Football Association|website=Twitter|date=31 December 2023|access-date=1 January 2024|language=ar}}</ref> He started in all three group stage games and then in two knockout stage games against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] and [[Tajikistan national football team|Tajikistan]], before missing out the semi-finals due to yellow card accumulation.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jordan reach final of Asian Cup after historic win against South Korea|date=6 February 2024|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/feb/06/jordan-reach-final-of-asian-cup-after-historic-win-against-south-korea|publisher=The Guardian}}</ref> Despite having no goals during the competition, Olwan's ability to hold the ball and dribble in tight spaces made him a threat to the opponent's defense, liberating spaces for his teammates to score.<ref>{{Cite web|date=1  February 2024|title=علي علوان يجني ثمار التألق الآسيوي مع "النشامى" بعقد احترافي جديد|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/sport/%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AB%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%8A-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF|access-date=7 February 2024|website=alaraby.co.uk|language=ar}}</ref>

On 5 June 2025, he netted his second international hat-trick in a 3–0 away win over [[Oman national football team|Oman]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]], securing his nation's first-ever participation in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.omanobserver.om/article/1171603/sports/football/ali-olwan-hits-hat-trick-as-jordan-blank-oman |title=Ali Olwan hits hat-trick as Jordan blank Oman |publisher=Oman Observer |date=5 June 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.royanews.tv/news/60225 |title=Jordan qualifies for 2026 FIFA World Cup for first time |publisher=Roya News |date=5 June 2025 }}</ref>

